// Brusselator - Recasting to Unimonomial Form
// Related: test_models1/m22_Brusselator.ant
// Source: Hernandez-Bermejo, Fairen & Brenig, "Algebraic recasting of nonlinear
//         systems of ODEs into universal formats"
//         J. Phys. A: Math. Gen. 31:2415-2430 (1998)
//         Section 4.2, Equations (45)-(54)
//
// The Brusselator (Nicolis & Prigogine 1977) is a model system for the
// Belousov-Zhabotinskii reaction showing limit cycle oscillations.
//
// Original QP form (Eq. 45):
//   x1' = x1*[-(b+1) + x1*x2 + a*x1^(-1)]
//   x2' = x2*[b*x1*x2^(-1) - x1^2]
//
// This is NOT a standard chemical kinetics form - it's already in QP format.
// Expanded to standard form:
//   x1' = a - (b+1)*x1 + x1^2*x2
//   x2' = b*x1 - x1^2*x2
//
// ==============================================================================
// EXACT RECASTING TO UNIMONOMIAL FORM (Eq. 49):
// ==============================================================================
// Via unimonomial embedding (2 -> 4 variables), system becomes:
//   z1' = z1*[-(b+1) + z1*z2^b*z3^a*z4^(-1)]
//   z2' = z2*[z1*z2^(-b)*z3^a*z4]
//   z3' = z3*[z1^(-1)*z3^(-a)]
//   z4' = z4*[z1^2*z3^(2a)]
//
// First integral introduced: z1^(1/2)*z3 = const
// Only one nonlinear term per equation (maximal simplification).
// ==============================================================================

model HBF1998_brusselator()
  // State variables
  compartment cell = 1
  var species x1 in cell
  var species x2 in cell

  // Parameters (typical values for limit cycle)
  a = 1.0
  b = 3.0
  
  // ORIGINAL ODEs (standard Brusselator)
  // Trimolecular reaction model: A -> X, B + X -> Y + D, 2X + Y -> 3X, X -> E
  x1' = a - (b + 1) * x1 + x1^2 * x2
  x2' = b * x1 - x1^2 * x2
  
  // Initial conditions (off steady state for oscillation)
  x1 = 1.5
  x2 = 3.0
end
// @SIM T_START=0 T_END=20 N_STEPS=400 EPS_INIT=1e-6
// Note: Zero-valued initial conditions are replaced with EPS_INIT during recasting.
